Defendant Glen D Voden in court with attorney Eryn M Menden.  David John Behm appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

Count #1:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

 6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT  (Apply 2 Days Credit if revoked)
 3 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT;
 3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

*D/L REVOCATION:  36 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel:  Completed on 1/20/16.
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*Perform 100 Hours Community Service. 
*6 Months of Day Report Center consecutive to condition time. 

FINE:  $1569.00 (apply cash bail and balance to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE: $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  12 MONTHS NON WORKING HOURS w/Standard Release Conditions including release for community service and treatment.  Defendant remanded into custody and sentence to begin forthwith.  

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
